        <Parent_String>bagpipes [300042405], reedpipes with multiple pipes [300224176], reedpipes (confined aerophones) [300042558], reeds (aerophones) [300193013], aerophones [300041622], sound devices by acoustical characteristics [300041621], sound devices (equipment) [300387677], Sound Devices (hierarchy name) [300041619], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Irish bellows-blown bagpipes, dating in their present form back to the 18th century, having a double-reed chanter, three single-reed drone pipes in one stock, and three or four keyed double-reed pipes for playing chords. The instruments are played sitting with the drones lying across the player's knees.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gaitas irlandesas de fuelles, que datan en su forma actual desde el siglo XVIII, consistentes en un tubo melódico con lengüeta doble, tres roncones con lengüetas sencillas montados en un mástil, y tres o cuatro tubos con lengüeta doble y llaves para tocar acordes. Estos instrumentos se ejecutan con el intérprete sentado, y los roncones descansando sobre sus rodillas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Doedelzakken met 1 speelpijp met dubbel riet, 3 bourdons met enkel riet in één blok, 3 of 4 dubbelrietpijpen met kleppen waar akkoorden op kunnen worden gespeeld, met blaasbalgen aangeblazen; Ierland, 18de eeuw.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>以風袋送風演奏的愛爾蘭風笛，歷史可回溯至十八世紀。有一雙簧調音管、三根固定於同一木柄的單簧單音管、三或四根演奏和弦的有鍵雙簧吹管。演奏者坐著吹奏，並將單音管擺放於膝上。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Irische balggeblasene Sackpfeife, die in der jetzigen Form auf das 18. Jahrhundert zurückgeht; mit einer Melodiepfeife mit Doppelrohrblatt und drei Bordunpfeifen mit Einfachrohrblättern in einer Halterung sowie drei oder vier Pfeifen mit Doppelrohrblatt und Klappen, um Akkorde zu spielen. Das Instrument wird im Sitzen gespielt, wobei die Bordunpfeifen über den Knien des Spielers liegen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
